{"id": 239774674, "title": "My favourite room: \u2018I told the builder to make an indent big enough for a bottle of wine in the steam room\u2019 \u2014", "text": "Couples whose kids have flown the nest tend to downsize when their family homes get too big for them. And the clever thing to do when downsizing, or \u2018rightsizing\u2019 as it\u2019s called now, is to future-proof the new home to ensure it\u2019s still suitable when people age and maybe can\u2019t manage things like stairs. Most rightsizers therefore opt for an apartment with a lift or a single-storey house. But Dublin couple Martin Stairs and Edel Noble did the opposite \u2014 they bought a single-storey cottage and added a staircase. This has nothing to do with the fact that their surname is Stairs, or rather, Martin\u2019s is: \u201cI held on to my maiden name Noble because it\u2019s nicer,\u201d Edel is quick to say.", "summary": "<p>Couples whose kids have flown the nest tend to downsize when their family homes get too big for them. And the clever thing to do when downsizing, or \u2018rightsizing\u2019 as it\u2019s called now, is to future-proof the new home to ensure it\u2019s still suitable when people age and maybe can\u2019t manage things like stairs.</p>", "url": "https://www.independent.ie/life/home-garden/interiors/my-favourite-room-i-told-the-builder-to-make-an-indent-big-enough-for-a-bottle-of-wine-in-the-steam-room-one-couples-luxury-bungalow-renovation/a976802226.html", "image": "https://focus.independent.ie/thumbor/y_MkWBev44-I9zgFrJj67mUWKWU=/0x0:3237x2158/550x550/prod-mh-ireland/882e5958-f5a8-4fcc-9268-a76ad6e3bdf2/ccaa6ff8-bf89-4f09-9c29-8bdd74257c36/882e5958-f5a8-4fcc-9268-a76ad6e3bdf2.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-23 01:30:00", "author": "Mary O'sullivan", "authors": ["Mary O'sullivan"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ie", "sentiment": 0.036}